    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ecological or environmental areas that are inhabited by particular species of animals or plants and contain the materials and conditions necessary for their survival. For the aggregates of influences affecting organisms, use "environments (object groupings)." For areas set apart as protected for plants or animals, use "wildlife refuges."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000011801/Morrow, Dictionary of Landscape Architecture (1987)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052118/Abercrombie et al, Dictionary of Biology (1966)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para la localización tradicional y usual de una planta o animal; para las influencias agregadas que afectan los organismos, use "ambiente (grupo de objetos)".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Te gebruiken voor de traditionele en gebruikelijke leefomgeving van een plant of dier; gebruik 'milieus (objectgroepen)' voor het geheel van invloeden op organismen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
